Method behavioural specifications:
- The integer array parameter `nums` must not be null.
- The integer parameter `key` must be an integer from the integer array `nums`.
- The integer parameter `k` is greater than or equal to 1 and is less than or equal to the length of the integer array `nums`.
- The integer collection result contains all k-distant indices sorted in increasing order.
- For each k-distant index `i` in the result, there exists at least one index `j` such that `|i - j| <= k` and `nums[j] == key`.